<http://www.spektrix.com/thecultch/event/131001AKLPDKCKNJTRJJKCSJNQLPBJRQH> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Popurrí";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Plastik Theatriks</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Vancity Culture Lab 1895 Venables St. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Popurrí is a physical theatre piece that draws upon clowning, puppetry, masks, and opera to create a variety of short vignettes. Weaving together absurdity, surreal atmospheres, and eccentric characters. Developed through workshops and performances across Victoria, BC, including Atomic Vaudeville's cabarets, SKAMpede Festival 2025 and more, Popurrí made its official debut at the Victoria Fringe Festival 2025, thanks to the generous BC Arts Council.At the Fringe, Popurrí was the Volunteer Pick, and it recieved outstanding feedback and reviews.<span><br/></span>Popurrí invites audiences into a playful and oniric world. It's ok to be confused.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Audience Advisory</span>: Nudity, staged violence (including a knife fight), depictions of suicide and death, simulated gore and simulated vomiting<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Talkback</span>: May 30<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-28T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
